Using outdated dependencies is one of the most common security vulnerabilities. CVE-2021-3129 in Laravel's Ignition package allowed remote code execution on thousands of servers because developers didn't update their packages. Here's how to manage dependencies safely.

**VULNERABLE CONFIGURATION**:

```php
<?php
// composer.json with dangerous version constraints
// This allows any version, including vulnerable ones
{
    "name": "myapp/vulnerable-app",
    "require": {
        "php": ">=7.2",
        "laravel/framework": "*",
        "facade/ignition": "*",
        "guzzlehttp/guzzle": ">=6.0",
        "phpmailer/phpmailer": "^5.0",
        "monolog/monolog": "*"
    },
    "config": {
        "preferred-install": "dist"
    }
}
```

